> We made a classic "fancy" chicken dish weeknight-ready! Simply combine oregano-seasoned chicken, green olives, lemon, raisins, and vinegar in our convenient recyclable oven tray, and bake. Serve this sweet, tangy, briny, garlicky goodness over a hearty, lemony grain blend with a sprinkle of herbaceous parsley, and it's party time!

== Preparation ==

Adjust #rack{} to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @green olives{1}(chopped). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked) leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

== Chicken Marbella ==

In #oven-ready tray{}, mix together olives, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, juice from one lemon wedge, @salt{}, and @pepper{} until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings, divide ingredients between two trays, using a large drizzle of olive oil and juice from one lemon wedge for each tray.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Place chicken over sauce mixture in tray.

> For 4 servings, divide chicken between trays.

Sprinkle tops of chicken with @brown sugar{1%tbsp}. Bake on top rack (be sure your oven has preheated!) until chicken is cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, bake two trays side by side on top rack.

== Microwavable Grain Blend ==

When chicken has 5 minutes left, massage @microwavable grain blend{1%unit} in package to break up grains; partially open package. Microwave until warmed through, ~{60-90%seconds}.

Transfer to a #medium bowl{}; stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, half the lemon zest, and @butter{1%tbsp}. Stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

== To Serve ==

Sprinkle chicken with parsley and remaining lemon zest.

Divide chicken and grains between plates; serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.